Hi!

Thanks for being part of the Font Awesome Community.

I think the issue is in the javascript function that is managing the toggle status

```js
    $('section.box-categories .nav-panel li a').on('click', function(e) {
        if ($(e.target).hasClass("nav-toggle")) {
            $(e.delegateTarget)
                .parent('li')
                .find('> ul.nav').toggle();
            return false;
        }
    });
```

The `path` element doesn't have the nav-toggle class, so the event will be propagated up.

I will be go for

```js
    $('section.box-categories .nav-panel li a .nav-toggle').on('click', function(e) {
        $(e.delegateTarget)
            .parent('li')
            .find('> ul.nav').toggle();
        return false;
    });
```

Anyway, this is not related to font awesome

Closing here

