We released conda 4.3 in January, and in that release we removed package signing support altogether.  Largely because of discussion here, we were concerned that its existence provided an illusion of security that was worse than not having it at all.

I'm working on wrapping up conda 4.4.0 into a canary release, and after we get conda 4.4 released to GA, my next big feature development project will probably be working on TUF implementation.

